<LegalPageLayout
  title="Editorial & AI policy"
  description="Faktum AI editorial standards and AI-assisted production disclosure."
  path="/en/editorial/"
>
  <p><strong>Last updated:</strong> 2026-05-24</p>

  <h2>Editorial line</h2>
  <p>
    Faktum AI is a Finnish AI news and analysis site. We publish news, analysis, interview summaries,
    and tool reviews — source-backed, without hype.
  </p>

  <h2>AI-assisted production</h2>
  <p>Faktum AI uses AI tools (including Cursor and language models) for:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Source analysis and structuring</li>
    <li>Drafts and translations (FI ↔ EN)</li>
    <li>Visual planning and metadata</li>
    <li>Site engineering</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    <strong>A human reviews and approves</strong> every publication before it goes live. Articles are
    not published automatically.
  </p>

  <h2>Sources</h2>
  <p>Every article includes a source list. Claims are separated from interpretation. Uncertainty is flagged.</p>

  <h2>Commercial content</h2>
  <p>Partnerships, sponsored pieces, and ads are labelled clearly on the article.</p>

  <h2>Corrections</h2>
  <p>Errors are corrected in the article with an updated timestamp. Significant fixes may be noted in the newsletter.</p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p><a href="mailto:marko@faktum-ai.com">marko@faktum-ai.com</a></p>
</LegalPageLayout>
